================================================================================
  SCREENSHOT 6: TEAM COLLABORATION
================================================================================

  SCREEN SHOWN:
  Team workspace view showing:
  - Team name header: "Design Team" or "Engineering"
  - Shared project with assigned members (avatar circles)
  - Task list with assignee avatars next to each task
  - Team progress bar: "Team completion: 78%"
  - Member activity indicators (online/offline dots)
  - "Invite member" button visible

  APP STATE:
  - 4-5 team members visible (avatar circles with initials)
  - Mixed task states: some completed, some in progress, some upcoming
  - Team analytics summary card visible
  - Collaborative feel without being cluttered

  TEXT OVERLAY:
  Headline:    "TEAMS THAT SHIP."
  Subheadline: "Shared tasks, analytics, and escalation chains."

  NOTES:
  - Show enough team members to communicate "collaboration" without clutter
  - Use diverse avatar colors (pulled from brand palette: violet, gold, etc.)
  - The team view should feel professional but not enterprise-dull
  - This screenshot targets the Team plan upsell

================================================================================
  SCREENSHOT ORDER & RATIONALE
================================================================================

  1. Home Screen      -- Immediate comprehension: "This is a task manager"
  2. Multi-Channel    -- Key differentiator: "This is not like other task apps"
  3. Ghost Mode       -- Unique feature: "Focus mode that is actually cool"
  4. Progress Hub     -- Gamification hook: "I want those streaks"
  5. Daily Wisdom     -- Emotional hook: "This app cares about my growth"
  6. Team View        -- Expansion: "My team could use this too"

  This order follows the AIDA model:
  - Attention (1-2): What is it + why is it different
  - Interest (3-4): Unique features that intrigue
  - Desire (5): Emotional connection
  - Action (6): Team upsell / expansion

================================================================================
  LOCALIZATION NOTES
================================================================================

  For India (Hindi):
  - Translate text overlays to Hindi
  - Use INR pricing in Team screenshot: "Rs 149/mo"
  - Daily Wisdom screenshot should show a Hindi quote option
  - WhatsApp should be the first channel shown (highest usage in India)

  For other markets:
  - Prioritize channels by regional popularity
  - Japan/Korea: LINE integration screenshot (future)
  - Brazil: WhatsApp first
  - US/EU: Email and Slack first

